sentences: Heather Lewis (born 1962) is an American multi-instrumentalist and founding member of Beat Happening.
Prior to her work with Beat Happening, Lewis was a member of the Supreme Cool Beings, who are notable for having the first ever release on K Records, 1982's Survival of the Coolest.
Lewis grew up in Westchester County, New York, and left to attend Evergreen College in Olympia, Washington in 1980.
During a summer break at Evergreen in 1982, Lewis was visiting her friend Gary May's apartment.
She appeared as a guest vocalist on several songs from Land of the Loops, as well as The Wedding Present's album Watusi.
